<paragraph id="8B933683FF9DFFC6FFC8FA8FFBA2FAE9" blockId="1.[96,1064,1365,1396]" box="[96,1064,1365,1396]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="B958EA91FF9DFFC6FFC8FA8FFF6BFAEE" box="[96,225,1365,1395]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. For diagnostic features of this species see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBD4B72FF9DFFC6FC98FA8DFBA9FAE9" author="Wang, C. &amp; S. Q. Li" box="[816,1059,1366,1396]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="25 - 57" refId="ref1963" refString="Wang, C. and S. Q. Li. 2020. On eight species of jumping spiders from Xishuangbanna, Yunnan, China (Araneae, Salticidae). ZooKeys 909: 25 - 57." type="journal article" year="2020">Wang &amp; Li (2020)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B933683FF9DFFC5FFC8FA45FC06FEA6" blockId="1.[96,1536,1439,1995]" lastBlockId="2.[96,1535,173,315]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="B958EA91FF9DFFC6FFC8FA45FE42FA23" box="[96,456,1439,1470]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Supplementary description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B958EA91FF9DFFC6FE49FA7AFDAEFA23" box="[481,548,1440,1470]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13172A06FF9DFFC6FD9CFA7BFD54FA22" box="[564,734,1441,1471]" captionStart="Figures 1–7" captionStartId="2.[240,333,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[240,1392,615,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-213@2.[240,1392,612,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1–7. Male Dexippus pengi from Meghalaya, India. 1, Dorsal view. 2, Left lateral view. 3, Frontal view. 4, Chelicerae, posterior view. 5, Left pedipalp, ventral view. 6, Same, retrolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533690/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Figures 1–7</figureCitation>
). Carapace brick red, covered with black appressed hairs, laterally provided with broad bands of white hairs (
<figureCitation id="13172A06FF9DFFC6FC8CFA1DFC46FA79" box="[804,972,1479,1508]" captionStart="Figures 1–7" captionStartId="2.[240,333,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[240,1392,615,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-213@2.[240,1392,612,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1–7. Male Dexippus pengi from Meghalaya, India. 1, Dorsal view. 2, Left lateral view. 3, Frontal view. 4, Chelicerae, posterior view. 5, Left pedipalp, ventral view. 6, Same, retrolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533690/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Figures 1–2</figureCitation>
). Eye field dark, covered with appressed black hairs intermixed with long black hairs; rim of eyes with golden brown hairs. Fovea narrow, straight, longitudinal, reddish-brown. Clypeus low, covered with white setae (
<figureCitation id="13172A06FF9DFFC6FBECF9C8FB7FF9B2" box="[1092,1269,1554,1583]" captionStart="Figures 1–7" captionStartId="2.[240,333,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[240,1392,615,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-213@2.[240,1392,612,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1–7. Male Dexippus pengi from Meghalaya, India. 1, Dorsal view. 2, Left lateral view. 3, Frontal view. 4, Chelicerae, posterior view. 5, Left pedipalp, ventral view. 6, Same, retrolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533690/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Figures 1, 3</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae long, robust; promargin with two teeth (proximal small and distal large), retromargin with a single large tooth (
<figureCitation id="13172A06FF9DFFC6FFC1F987FF6EF9E7" box="[105,228,1629,1658]" captionStart="Figures 1–7" captionStartId="2.[240,333,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[240,1392,615,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-213@2.[240,1392,612,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1–7. Male Dexippus pengi from Meghalaya, India. 1, Dorsal view. 2, Left lateral view. 3, Frontal view. 4, Chelicerae, posterior view. 5, Left pedipalp, ventral view. 6, Same, retrolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533690/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Figure 4</figureCitation>
). Labium and endites reddish-brown with pale white tips. Sternum yellowish-brown, covered with grey hairs. Opisthosoma elongate-ovoid, yellowish with black markings on dorsum and sides forming numerous pale yellowish speckles, posteriorly with a chevron pattern (
<figureCitation id="13172A06FF9DFFC6FB72F972FA01F958" box="[1242,1419,1704,1733]" captionStart="Figures 1–7" captionStartId="2.[240,333,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[240,1392,615,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-213@2.[240,1392,612,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1–7. Male Dexippus pengi from Meghalaya, India. 1, Dorsal view. 2, Left lateral view. 3, Frontal view. 4, Chelicerae, posterior view. 5, Left pedipalp, ventral view. 6, Same, retrolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533690/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Figures 1–2</figureCitation>
); venter creamy-yellow. Legs reddish-brown; I–II robust with white patches on patellae. Spinnerets creamy yellow with black longitudinal stripes, covered with white hairs. Body length 5.25. Carapace 2.49 long, 1.91 wide. Opisthosoma 2.76 long, 1.36 wide. Ocular area 1.12 long, 1.61 wide. Eye diameters and intraocular distances: AME 0.56, ALE 0.29, PME 0.07, PLE 0.31; AME–AME 0.02, AME–ALE 0.02, PME– PME 1.49, ALE–ALE 1.15, PME–PLE 0.25, PLE–PLE 1.36, ALE–PME 0.26, ALE-PLE 0.58. Chelicerae 0.91 long. Clypeus 0.03 high. Sternum 0.94 long, 0.67 wide. Measurements of pedipalp and legs: pedipalp 2.07 [0.79, 0.30, 0.31, 0.67], leg I 4.54 [1.46, 0.73, 1.11, 0.75, 0.49], leg II 3.94 [1.32, 0.61, 0.90, 0.65, 0.46], leg III 4.67 [1.55, 0.63, 0.98, 0.97, 0.54], leg IV 4.89 [1.53, 0.63, 1.03, 1.10, 0.60]. Leg formula: 4312. Spination of pedipalp and legs: pedipalp femur I–II pld 2 do 3, III–IV pld 2 do 3 rld 1; patella I–II pl 1, III– VI pl 1 rl 1; tibia I–II pld1 pl 2 plv 3 rlv 3, III–IV pld 1 pl 2 plv 3 rld 2 rl 1 rlv 3; metatarsus I–II pl 1 plv 2 rlv 2, III–IV pld 2 pl 1 plv 2 rld 2 rl 1 rlv 2; tarsus I–IV spineless.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B933683FF9EFFC5FFC8FEB3FA5AFE4C" blockId="2.[96,1536,361,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Pedipalp (
<figureCitation id="13172A06FF9EFFC5FF45FEB3FE1CFE1B" box="[237,406,361,390]" captionStart="Figures 1–7" captionStartId="2.[240,333,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[240,1392,615,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-213@2.[240,1392,612,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1–7. Male Dexippus pengi from Meghalaya, India. 1, Dorsal view. 2, Left lateral view. 3, Frontal view. 4, Chelicerae, posterior view. 5, Left pedipalp, ventral view. 6, Same, retrolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533690/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Figures 5–7</figureCitation>
) segments brown. RTA short, broad, with angular apex having slight prolateral curvature, with a small retrolateral thorny protrusion (
<figureCitation id="13172A06FF9EFFC5FCDEFE54FBAFFE36" box="[886,1061,398,427]" captionStart="Figures 1–7" captionStartId="2.[240,333,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[240,1392,615,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-213@2.[240,1392,612,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1–7. Male Dexippus pengi from Meghalaya, India. 1, Dorsal view. 2, Left lateral view. 3, Frontal view. 4, Chelicerae, posterior view. 5, Left pedipalp, ventral view. 6, Same, retrolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533690/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Figures 5–7</figureCitation>
). Bulb almost round (
<figureCitation id="13172A06FF9EFFC5FAD8FE54FA67FE36" box="[1392,1517,398,427]" captionStart="Figures 1–7" captionStartId="2.[240,333,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[240,1392,615,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-213@2.[240,1392,612,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1–7. Male Dexippus pengi from Meghalaya, India. 1, Dorsal view. 2, Left lateral view. 3, Frontal view. 4, Chelicerae, posterior view. 5, Left pedipalp, ventral view. 6, Same, retrolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533690/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Figure 5</figureCitation>
); embolus stout, originating apicoprolaterally, curved retrolaterally, with upward directed tip (
<figureCitation id="13172A06FF9EFFC5FAE0FE6EFA34FE4C" box="[1352,1470,436,465]" captionStart="Figures 1–7" captionStartId="2.[240,333,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[240,1392,615,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-213@2.[240,1392,612,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 1–7. Male Dexippus pengi from Meghalaya, India. 1, Dorsal view. 2, Left lateral view. 3, Frontal view. 4, Chelicerae, posterior view. 5, Left pedipalp, ventral view. 6, Same, retrolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6533690" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6533690/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Figure 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B933683FF9EFFC5FFC8FE27FBF6FD81" blockId="2.[96,1148,509,540]" box="[96,1148,509,540]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
